# Copy to `.env` and fill in.
#
# ⚠️ Only VITE_-prefixed vars reach the browser, and everything here is COMPILED
# INTO THE PUBLIC BUNDLE. Anyone can read it with devtools. Never put a secret in
# this file — no client secrets, no API secrets, no database URLs. Those belong in
# hrm-backend/.env, which never leaves the server.

# --- Google OAuth -----------------------------------------------------------
# The client *ID* is public by design and safe here. The client *SECRET* is not —
# it goes in hrm-backend/.env as GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET.
# Google Cloud Console → APIs & Services → Credentials → OAuth client ID (Web).
# Add http://localhost:5173 as an authorised JavaScript origin.
# Until this is set, the Google button falls back to the simulated chooser.
VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=

# --- Backend ----------------------------------------------------------------
# Base URL of the NestJS API. Leave BLANK to run the app entirely on mock data
# (which is how the Vercel demo runs — it has no backend).
# Local development: http://localhost:3000
VITE_API_BASE_URL=

# --- Cloudinary (Phase 2 — file uploads) ------------------------------------
# Only these two are safe in the browser, and only for *unsigned* uploads.
# The API key and API secret must NEVER appear here — they live in the backend,
# which signs each upload. An unsigned preset is the only browser-safe path.
VITE_CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME=
VITE_CLOUDINARY_UPLOAD_PRESET=
